}}</ref>在退出中国事件之前，用户在Google中国版搜索[[政治|政治]]敏感或色情（如：[[性_(生物學)|性]]、[[粗口|粗口]]词句）等内容时，会在网页尾部显示“据当地法律法规和政策，部分搜索结果未予显示”，同时过滤了不符合规定的搜索结果。Google也证实其被迫协助中国政府进行网络审查，<ref>Liedtke, Michael. "[http://www.breitbart.com/news/2006/01/24/D8FBCF686.html Google Agrees to Censor Results in China] {{Wayback|url=http://www.breitbart.com/news/2006/01/24/D8FBCF686.html |date=20060621144316 }}." ''[http://www.breitbart.com/ Breitbart.com] {{Wayback|url=http://www.breitbart.com/ |date=20100927110004 }}.'' 2006-01-24.</ref>但其不向中国政府提供用户的搜索记录等信息。<ref name="TEGGO">{{cite web|author=Marc Gunther|url=http://money.cnn.com/2006/02/15/news/international/pluggedin_fortune/index.htm?cnn=yes|title=Tech execs get grilled over China business|work=CNN Money|date=2006-02-16|accessdate=2010-09-29|archive-date=2008-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011132834/http://money.cnn.com/2006/02/15/news/international/pluggedin_fortune/index.htm?cnn=yes|dead-url=no}}</ref>

